v><div><span></span></div><div>Link to article: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC2176051/</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/5c6sWrR</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[CyrusR21]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>But this isn’t better</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/5K7pASY</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/UKysj81.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>You see how this isn’t better, right?</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/5K7pASY</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[malbec]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Fuck this and fuck America</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/4o2phr2</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/hLXmFlB.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/4o2phr2</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[ygolordned]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Heard you weirdos like old timey historical photos.</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/zChua2W</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/1pXdS6E.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Found all these in an ancient family photo album. Not sure who most of the people are but I understand I’m related to most of them. This photo strikes me because of the date. 3 days before the stock market crash. Look at how carefree they were.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/basU48q.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>A relative wearing his uniform from WW1.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/Ylgfdwp.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Apparently I had a great aunt who died in childbirth. The baby boy was going to be named Aloysius. Neither of them survived. Her remaining children often visited the grave of their mother.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/jeBfsxJ.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>The writing on this photo is pretty self explanatory.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/YgsBzIv.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>It’s fun to think about people having pets more than 100 years ago. And guinea pigs no less!</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/FunJMcK.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>This photo is from the early 1920s. People were looking pretty fly for a hike!</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/BT8UrBt.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Just guys being dudes.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/wMLWSZw.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>This one struck me because that’s actually my grandfather on the left. I’ll be hiking at Mount Baldy this week for the first time. It’s been almost 100 years since that photo. As far as I know no member of my family has been there since.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/7mqfwOK.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Gotta love the beachwear.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/oNOF02w.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>I wish I had more context for this photo. The film “A League of Their Own” comes to mind. “Marla Hooch...what a hitter!!”</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/hyxLNxJ.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Just a sled ride in the Southern California mountains.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/bADzN60.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Snow day!</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/KIxwbWI.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>This photo is from 1907 or 1908.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/2UNYCJa.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Feed a deer? Why not?</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/aYEkvF2.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>I like knowing that even more than 100 years ago people were still total goofballs.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/ZuFkQyN.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>I’d love to know what they ate at that picnic.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/IdnvqNX.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Cold beer is timeless.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/PykbDOw.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Every always seemed dressed up.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/QC3RqNK.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>I bet they were up to no good.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/ZgxcW7E.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>A beer and a smoke. Unwinding after a long day.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/dTDDtuU.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Classy car.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/DZHzTlY.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Santa Monica has changed A LOT since this photo was taken.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/nzAJHc6.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Dog tax!!!</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/zChua2W</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[idonotsow]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Reminder:</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/Pbk07gt</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.c